# GitHub Markdown Style

When writing any markdown, always use **GitHub Flavored Markdown** (GFM) conventions:

- Use `> [!NOTE]`, `> [!TIP]`, `> [!IMPORTANT]`, `> [!WARNING]`, and `> [!CAUTION]` for callout blocks.
- Use `|` pipe tables with aligned dashes (`:---`, `:---:`, `---:`) for tabular data.
- Use `~~strikethrough~~` for strikethrough text.
- Use task list syntax: `- [ ]` and `- [x]` for checklists.
- Use triple backtick fenced code blocks with a language tag (e.g. ```markdown, ```yaml, ```bash).
- Use `[text](url)` for links and `![alt](url)` for images.
- Use `**bold**` and `*italic*` (not underscores for emphasis).
- Use `#` headings with a space after the `#`.
- Use `---` for horizontal rules.
- Use `<!-- -->` for HTML comments when needed.
- Stick to one blank line between blocks; avoid excessive whitespace.
